public static <IN> com.github.dm.jrt.ext.channel.ChannelsBuilder<? extends com.github.dm.jrt.channel.IOChannel<com.github.dm.jrt.ext.channel.Selectable<? extends IN>>> combine(@NotNull
                                                                                                                                                                        android.support.v4.util.SparseArrayCompat<? extends com.github.dm.jrt.channel.Channel.InputChannel<? extends IN>> channels)
        Returns a builder of input channels combining the specified channels into a selectable one. The selectable indexes will be the keys of the specified map.
        Note that the builder will successfully create only one input channel instance, and that the returned channel must be explicitly closed in order to ensure the completion of the invocation lifecycle.
        Type Parameters:
        IN - the input data type.
        Parameters:
        channels - the map of indexes and input channels.
        Returns:
        the selectable I/O channel builder.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified map is empty.
        See Also:
        Channels.combine(Map)

        Returns a builder of output channels merging the specified channels into a selectable one. The selectable indexes will be the keys of the specified sparse array.
